<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suns Tie Playoff Futility Record  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Phoenix Suns, facing elimination from the
NBA playoffs, tied a playoff record for futility in a half Tuesday
night, scoring 23 points against the Los Angeles Lakers.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns, who scored 71 points in the first half in beating the
Lakers 117-98 in Phoenix on Sunday to force a fifth game, trailed
49-23 at halftime Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The 23 points matched the mark set by the Utah Jazz in the
second half of a 96-54 loss to Chicago Bulls on June 7, 1998. The
54 points are the playoff record for a game.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns also tied the playoff record for futility in a second
quarter, when they scored nine points to the Lakers' 28.
</P>
<P>
   Phoenix shot 2-of-17 in the second quarter (11.8 percent), and
8-of-37 in the half (21.6 percent).
</P>
<P>
   Cliff Robinson led the Suns in scoring in the half with five
points.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers entered the game with a 3-1 lead in the best-of-seven
Western Conference semifinals and in need of one win to put them in
the conference finals against the Portland Trail Blazers.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers had two 10-0 spurts in the second quarter to give
them a 40-23 lead. Phoenix didn't have a field goal for over six
minutes while being outscored 17-3 at the end of the first quarter
and start of the second.
</P>
<P>
   The NBA record for fewest points in a half in a regular season
game is 19 by the Los Angeles Clippers against the Lakers last Dec.
14.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-17-00 0025 </TRAILER>
