<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-17 00:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CarsDirect.com Files for IPO  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- CarsDirect.com Inc., which sells cars and
related products over the Internet, has filed for an initial public
offering of stock.
</P>
<P>
   The company, based in Culver City, said it will use the $135.5
million it expects to clear from the offering on advertising,
operations and to reduce debt.
</P>
<P>
   The company was founded in 1998 and had a net loss of $72.3
million in 1999, according to documents filed with the Securities
and Exchange Commission. The company had a net loss of $43.1
million in the first three months of this year on revenues of $98.6
million.
</P>
<P>
   CarsDirect.com said it has sold 12,885 cars online since its
inception, including 6,255 in the first three months of this year.
The average price of the cars sold was $22,815, the company said.
</P>
<P>
   In its registration statement, the company said it expects
losses ''for the foreseeable future'' and that a large number of
risk factors would affect its ''new and unproven business model.''
</P>
<P>
   The company has powerful backers, including the Pasadena-based
venture capital firm, idealab!, which controls about 66 percent of
the company, according to the SEC filing. Last November,
CarsDirect.com raised $280 million from private investors and
investment banks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-17-00 0039 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
