<HEADLINE> Two Dead in Ballpark Shooting  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   OZARK, Ala. (AP) -- A man walked into a baseball park Tuesday
night and shot to death his ex-wife and her boyfriend in front of
hundreds of children and their parents, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The man then shot and critically wounded himself.
</P>
<P>
   Police Chief Tony Spivey said the shooting stemmed from a
custody dispute. He said at least 200 people witnessed the shooting
at the Fuqua ballpark in Ozark, 75 miles southeast of Montgomery.
</P>
<P>
   The suspect used a 12-gauge shotgun and fired 10 shots at the
victims, WFSA-TV reported. When the shotgun jammed, he pulled out a
.22-caliber pistol and shot himself.
</P>
<P>
   ''We bring our kids to the ball field, ball is a big thing in
Ozark,'' witness Theresa Moates told the television station. ''It's
just scary.''
</P>
<P>
   The gunman was listed in critical condition late Tuesday.
Several bystanders were treated for shock at a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities were withholding the names of the victims and the
gunman.
</P>
</TEXT>
