<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Higher; Gold Lower  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was higher against most other major
currencies in European trading today. Gold fell.
</P>
<P>
   The euro was quoted at 89.11 cents, down from 90.47 cents
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Other dollar rates compared with late Tuesday: 109.53 Japanese
yen, down from 109.78; 1.7397 Swiss francs, up from 1.7152; and
1.4976 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4849
</P>
<P>
   The British pound was quoted at $1.4903, down from $1.4991.
</P>
<P>
   Based on euro rates, the dollar is worth: 2.1939 German marks,
up from 2.1611; 7.3579 French francs, up from 7.2481; 2.4719 Dutch
guilders, up from 2.4350; 2,171.92 Italian lire, up from 2,139.52
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading in New York, the euro was trading at 89.23
cents, the pound was quoted at $1.4923 and the dollar was trading
at 109.44 yen.
</P>
<P>
   Gold closed in London at $272.40 bid per troy ounce, down from
$275.60 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   In Zurich the bid price was $272.20, down from $275.10.
</P>
<P>
   Gold in Hong Kong fell $1.50 to close at $274.15 an ounce.
</P>
<P>
   Silver closed in London at $4.99 bid per troy ounce, down from
$5.07.
</P>
