<HEADLINE> Treasury To Aid Wildfire Victims  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Treasury Department said Wednesday it is
taking steps to help out some victims of wildfires in New Mexico
who own U.S. savings bonds.
</P>
<P>
   The department's Bureau of Public Debt said it is expediting
procedures for both the replacement, as well as the payment of
savings bonds for owners living in the counties of Los Alamos,
Sandoval and Santa Fe. Should additional counties be declared
disaster areas the special procedures for savings bonds owners will
apply to those areas, too, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
   The expedited procedures are effective immediately and will
remain in effect through June 30, the Bureau of Public Debt said.
</P>
