<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Dead After Ballpark Shooting  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   OZARK, Ala. (AP) -- A woman who was killed Tuesday night by her
ex-husband in a murder-suicide at a youth baseball park had filed
harassment charges against him just over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Ricky Gerald Todd Smith, 35, opened fire in front of more than
200 people, killing Diana Smith 32, and her date, Edward McQuinn
II, 35, before turning the gun on himself. He died Wednesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
   The Smiths were recently divorced, and Ricky Smith lost a
custody battle over the couple's two children, said police Chief
Tony Spivey. Diana Smith had filed harassment charges against her
ex-husband on Saturday, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Spivey said the couple's two boys were at the ballpark when the
shooting occurred. He didn't know if they witnessed the shooting.
</P>
<P>
   ''From the witness reports we have, the father did communicate
with one of the children,'' Spivey said. ''Then he went to his
truck to retrieve his weapon and started the shooting.''
</P>
<P>
   Ricky Smith shot McQuinn in the head with a 12-gauge shotgun, he
said, but the gun apparently malfunctioned when he tried to fire at
his ex-wife. Smith then shot her several times in the head with a
.22 caliber pistol, Spivey said.
</P>
<P>
   He said Diana Smith and McQuinn had just recently begun dating.
</P>
<P>
   The shootings happened at about 6:40 p.m. as children and
parents were gathering for evening games. As shots rang out,
witnesses said parents grabbed their children and ran for a nearby
wooded area.
</P>
<P>
   ''A large number of them are just in total shock and total
disbelief,'' Spivey said. ''And very obviously, we have a lot of
traumatized children and parents.''
</P>
<P>
   Wallace Alton, who lived next door to Ricky Smith and his
parents until a few years ago, recalled Smith was a member of a
Baptist church.
</P>
<P>
   ''Not too long ago, he was driving the church van on Sunday,
picking up children,'' Alton said. ''I thought everything was fine.
I don't understand it.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
