<HEADLINE> Man Arrested in Fatal Va. Bombing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- A man was arrested Wednesday and charged
with setting a bomb that killed a woman a month before she was to
give birth to his child 2{ years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Coleman Leake Johnson Jr., 29, was charged with murder in the
Dec. 3, 1997, pipe bomb blast that killed 24-year-old Tammy Lynn
Baker outside her apartment. The fetus also was killed. If
convicted of the federal charge, Johnson could face the death
penalty.
</P>
<P>
   ''He did not want to support this child and that was his motive
for committing this heinous crime,'' U.S. Attorney Robert P. Crouch
Jr. said at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson was indicted by a federal grand jury in Charlottesville
on Tuesday and was arrested at 9:45 a.m. Wednesday in his car in
Newport News. He was jailed in Newport News pending a bond hearing
Monday. It was not immediately clear whether he had an attorney.
</P>
<P>
   Neither federal, state nor local officials would discuss
evidence that led them to the suspect.
