<HEADLINE> Senate Aide Named MLB Lobbyist  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Lucy Calautti, North Dakota Sen. Byron
Dorgan's chief of staff, joined major league baseball Wednesday as
the organization's lobbyist.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm very, very excited about this opportunity. This is an
enormously wonderful opportunity,'' said Calautti, the wife of
North Dakota Sen. Kent Conrad.
</P>
<P>
   Calautti, 53, will work out of the Washington law office of
Baker &AMP; Hostetler and report to William Schweitzer, who will
coordinate all of baseball's government relations. Baseball closed
its D.C. lobbying office a few months ago.
</P>
<P>
