<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Banking Firm Buys Petco  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Petco Animal Supplies, Inc. agreed to be
acquired Wednesday by two private banking firms, for an estimated
$464.2 million in cash.
</P>
<P>
   A company organized by Leonard Green &AMP; Partners LP and Texas
Pacific Group will purchase the San Diego-based pet supply company
for $22 per share in cash, Petco said in a statement Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The firms will also assume about $136 million in Petco debt. The
transaction, which will take Petco private, is expected to be
completed by fall.
</P>
<P>
   ''We are enthusiastic about the prospects of Petco and excited
to play a role in the company's future growth,'' John Danhakl,
partner with Leonard Green &AMP; Partners, and Jonathan Coslet, partner
with Texas Pacific, said in a joint statement.
</P>
<P>
   The purchase must still be approved by stockholders and federal
regulations. The final agreement is expected to be reached this
fall.
</P>
<P>
   ''The transaction announced today fulfills our long-standing
commitment to deliver maximum value to our stockholders,'' Brian K.
Devine, Petco's chairman, president and CEO, said in a statement
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The announcement came on the same day that Petco reported first
quarter earnings were up 44 percent to $6.4 million, or 30 cents
per share, compared with $3.6 million, or 17 cents per share, in
the first quarter of last year.
</P>
<P>
   Sales for the quarter ending April 29 increased 15 percent to a
record $265.2 million from $229.7 million in the first quarter last
year.
</P>
<P>
   Petco's stock closed at $14.93}, up 25 cents, on the Nasdaq
Stock Market on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Leonard Green &AMP; Partners is a private Los Angeles-based merchant
banking firm specializing in organizing, structuring and sponsoring
management buy-outs, privatizations and recapitalizations. The
company has significant investments in the Liberty Group Publishing
Inc. newspaper chain, Rite Aid drug stores and vitamin manufacturer
Twinlabs Corp.
</P>
<P>
   Texas Pacific, based in Fort Worth, Texas, is a private
investment partnership.
</P>
<P>
   Petco has 503 stores in 39 states and the District of Columbia.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
