<HEADLINE> Ex-Kennedy Aide Has Porn Conviction  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- A former aide to Eunice Kennedy Shriver
was convicted Wednesday of distributing child pornography over the
Internet and traveling to Utah to have sex with a 12-year-old girl.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas J. Pearl faces a maximum of 10 years in prison when he's
sentenced July 26.
</P>
<P>
   Pearl, 40, testified he sent images of child pornography to an
Internet companion who turned out to be a licensed therapist and
former police officer.
</P>
<P>
   Pearl's attorney, Robert Breeze, argued his client was entrapped
by the woman, who may have manufactured a case against Pearl
because she hoped to get a job as a cyber-sex cop.
</P>
<P>
   Pearl, who lived in Maryland, was fired when the Kennedy family
learned of his arrest. Shriver is a sister of the late President
John F. Kennedy, the late Sen. Robert Kennedy and Sen. Edward
Kennedy, D-Mass.
</P>
