<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-17 22:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Woman Testifies in Atheist Case  </HEADLINE>
By JIM VERTUNO
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN (AP) -- The only person charged in the disappearance of
atheist Madalyn Murray O'Hair said he had been told the woman and
her family were killed, a federal investigator testified in court
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Gary Paul Karr, 52, gave investigators a written statement in
March 1999 that said another suspect, David Roland Waters,
acknowledged he had killed O'Hair and her son and granddaughter,
according to FBI agent Samuel Sykes Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Madalyn O'Hair, son Jon Garth Murray and granddaughter Robin all
disappeared from San Antonio in 1995 along with $500,000 in gold
coins. Investigators believe they were kidnapped and robbed before
they were killed and buried.
</P>
<P>
   An ex-con, Karr is charged with conspiracy to kidnap and extort
money from the O'Hairs. He faces up to life in prison.
</P>
<P>
   Karr told agents he drove Robin O'Hair's car to the Austin
airport and left it there ''to make it look like the O'Hairs, or at
least Robin, had willingly left Austin,'' Houston said.
</P>
<P>
   Houston was on the witness stand for about 30 minutes at the end
of the day as the prosecution presented some of its strongest
testimony in the case, although much of it centered on Waters, who
has not been charged.
</P>
<P>
   The agent said Karr also drew investigators a map of a South
Texas ranch where Karr believed their bodies were buried.
</P>
<P>
   About 100 agents searched the ranch in April 1999 but no bodies
were found.
</P>
<P>
   Karr also told investigators Waters recruited him to help the
O'Hairs flee the country to avoid problems with the Internal
Revenue Service.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators believe Waters masterminded the alleged plot. He
is serving 60 years in prison for stealing from the O'Hair's
atheist organizations and federal gun charges.
</P>
<P>
   Waters' ex-girlfriend, Patti Jo Steffens, testified for about
six hours and detailed bloody shoes she said she found in the
apartment they shared and that before she disappeared Waters
sometimes fantasized about torturing Madalyn O'Hair.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators believe the O'Hairs were dismembered and buried in
55-gallon drums.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
