<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-17 22:40 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Ed upholds rape and other charges against longtime school administrator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   PERU, N.Y. (AP) -- A veteran school administrator who spent the
last 12 years as assistant principal for discipline was fired
Tuesday after a state Education Department hearing officer upheld
many of the charges leveled against him by the school board.
</P>
<P>
   The Peru Central School Board made the announcement after
receiving a 73-page decision by SED Hearing Officer Paul S.
Zonderman. The decision upheld many of the 72 charges brought
against Junior-Senior High School Assistant Principal Stephen
Tolosky.
</P>
<P>
   In the report, Zonderman described Tolosky as ''sexually
aggressive and adulterous, particularly after a few drinks.''
</P>
<P>
   The most serious charge upheld by the hearing officer was of
raping a school employee in her home in 1988, a crime never
reported to police and for which the statute of limitations had run
out.
</P>
<P>
   Tolosky was also found guilty of sexually harassing employees,
having an adulterous, 10-year affair with a district employee of
which staff and students were aware; using profanity in front of
students; and income tax invasion.
</P>
<P>
   The 26-year district employee was suspended with pay from his
$72,133-a-year job in May 1999.
</P>
<P>
   In a written statement, Tolosky described the disciplinary
hearings as ''unfair'' and claimed he was not given the chance to
explain or defend himself.
</P>
<P>
   Thirty-four witnesses testified in behalf of Tolosky and the
school district during hearings held between Nov. 30, 1999 and
March 10.
</P>
<P>
   In recommending Tolosky's dismissal, Zonderman wrote, ''To be
sure, the district has searched far and wide to come up with an
expanded list of charges in an effort to discharge'' Tolosky.
</P>
<P>
   Nevertheless, he said, the district produced ''overwhelming
evidence that Tolosky is unfit to be a teacher or administrator in
the school system.''
</P>
<P>
   Peru is 9 miles south of Plattsburgh.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
